<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>More Details | TraceFI</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.5/font/bootstrap-icons.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
  <style>
    body {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0A0F24, #1B1F36);
      color: #ffffff;
      font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .details-container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 60px auto 0 auto;
      background: #111827;
      border-radius: 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 24px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
      padding: 40px 32px 32px 32px;
    }
    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      color: #60a5fa;
    }
    .details-container h2 {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .details-container ul, .details-container ol {
      color: #cbd5e1;
      margin-left: 1.2rem;
    }
    .details-container li {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .details-container p {
      color: #cbd5e1;
    }
    .btn-custom {
      background: #2563eb;
      color: #fff;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 10px 28px;
      margin-top: 2rem;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .btn-custom:hover {
      background: #1e40af;
      color: #fff;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="details-container">
    <h2>Platform Features & Benefits</h2>
    <div>
      <span class="section-title">What is TraceFI?</span>
      <p>TraceFI is a collaborative compliance and risk management platform for financial institutions. It enables secure client onboarding, risk assessment, and transparent multi-institution review, with automated notifications and audit trails.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="section-title">Key Features</span>
      <ul>
        <li>Client onboarding with automated risk scoring (geography, occupation, PEP, source of funds, etc.)</li>
        <li>Country risk and transaction monitoring dashboards</li>
        <li>Multi-institution workflow: FIs can propose, accept, or reject client risk status</li>
        <li>Rejection workflow with reason capture and notification</li>
        <li>Automated email alerts for risk status changes and actions</li>
        <li>Real-time in-app notifications for all relevant FIs</li>
        <li>Blockchain integration for auditability (optional, if enabled)</li>
        <li>Admin dashboard for compliance oversight and reporting</li>
        <li>Secure authentication and role-based access</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="section-title">How does it work?</span>
      <ol>
        <li>FIs register and log in to the platform</li>
        <li>Clients are added with detailed KYC and risk data</li>
        <li>Other FIs review, accept, or reject the proposed risk status (with reason if rejected)</li>
        <li>All responses trigger notifications and emails to the initiating FI</li>
        <li>All actions are logged for compliance and can be exported by admins</li>
        <li>Optional: Key actions are recorded on blockchain for tamper-proof audit trails</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div>
      <span class="section-title">Benefits</span>
      <ul>
        <li>Centralized, auditable compliance workflow</li>
        <li>Faster, more secure client onboarding and review</li>
        <li>Reduced risk of fraud, identity misuse, and money laundering</li>
        <li>Automated, real-time communication between FIs</li>
        <li>Comprehensive reporting and admin oversight</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-custom"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left"></i> Back to Home</a>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
